9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 281, O.S.L.
11 2023, as amended by Section 2, Chapter 408, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S.
12 Supp. 2025, Section 5-148.2), is amended to read as follows:
13 Section 5-148.2. A. There is hereby created in the State
14 Treasury a revolving fund for the State Department of Education to
15 be designated the “School Security Revolving Fund”. The fund shall
16 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
17 shall consist of all monies received by the State Department of
18 Education from:
19 1. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from other
20 state agencies and entities for school security;
21 2. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from the
22 United States government obligated to school security projects;
23 3. Gifts, donations, and bequests; and
24 4. Monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1189 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. All monies accruing to the credit of the School Security
2 Revolving Fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
3 expended by the State Department of Education for the purposes of:
4 1. Establishing and maintaining a School Resource Officer
5 Program; and
6 2. Providing physical security enhancements for schools
7 including, but not limited to, school resource officers, cameras,
8 gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security geofencing,
9 ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert systems.
10 Monies in the School Security Revolving Fund shall supplement
11 and not supplant existing school security funding.
12 C. Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall
13 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
14 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
15 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
16 Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall not
17 exceed Subject to the availability of funding, Fifty Million Dollars
18 ($50,000,000.00) in any fiscal year and shall be allocated from the
19 School Security Revolving Fund and divided equally among every
20 public school district in the this state each fiscal year for three
21 (3) fiscal years beginning July 1, 2026.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1189 SFLR Page 2
